east what’s there not to love come on people it’s michaels key to success the key to success is leveraging the talent of those around you bringing together a world class team and developing them and trying to be a fully integrated person i want to leverage and improve as a leader merchant mother spouse and friend i try and bring my whole self to work defining moment i can’t boil it down to a single moment there have definitely been stepping stone moments throughout my life that have lead me to where i am there have also been mentoring moments with great coaches the opening of the first store ever for a brand new company was very satisfying greatest challenge like most people life is full of professional and personal challenges you need to make a decision you are going to come out on the other side a stronger and wiser person and then plan accordingly proudest achievement i am most proud of the success of the people i have mentored watching them develop within companies and become great community leaders ultimate career goal my goal is to continue to learn grow as a leader and as a business professional business motto my personal business motto is “lead with yourself” mentors my greatest mentor is my mother she is an amazing woman her quiet strength and determination are an inspiration to me she instilled great values and a sense of responsibility in my brothers and sister and me she is very open minded and current in her way of thinking and in her view of the world rating the market i am new to the dallasfort worth area i have found it to be a welcoming atmosphere loaded with top notch executives industry outlook the craft and hobby industry has faired quite well during this economic down turn we certainly have not come out unscathed but we also haven’t suffered as badly as other retail channels many consumers are turning to home made and staying in with their families and doing projects together best advice be yourself leverage your strengths but be aware of your weaknesses you are ultimately in charge of your own development don’t wait for the official process giving back i am most rewarded by helping a cause in which i am personally connected i have led the effort to merge two aids service organizations and chaired the “go red for women” campaign while living in tampa bay after hours i love to spend time with my husband brian and my two children madison and clay favorite book i enjoy all books and i have very eclectic taste in books i can move from a business history book like giants of enterprise to trying to out pace my daughter through the twilight series on the web i don’t twitter but i am a chronic texter i watch the market through cnbc and hit the news through the usual suspects profile to mirror the passion of michaels’ customers president and chief operating officer shelley broader encourages creativity on the corporate side this includes each department decorating its own space now company headquarters’ walls are covered with murals of eagles ships and houses there are also a few chandeliers “it’s been really fun that’s really the essence of our brand — it’s fun it’s creative it’s lively” broader says “it’s passionate so you can’t have a regularlooking corporate office if you want to inspire those thoughts in your customers” broader who joined the company in june  comes to michaels stores inc during its reinvention to achieve the goal of making the brand customercentric stores are being reorganized to be more accommodating and inspiring the children’s area now includes educational activities in addition to art displays that group all related materials together also include craft ideas this contrasts with stores’ previous organization when customers had to search various sections to find all the supplies they needed brian c cornell michaels’ former chief executive and current president and chief executive of sam’s club recruited broader cornell sees broader as a “key catalyst” in transforming michaels to be more focused on the customer “she’s a very energetic dynamic candid business leader who can manage teams who can strategically identify the key areas of focus for an organization and who can get things done and done in the right way” cornell says besides michaels’ status as a household brand broader says the opportunity to learn a new class of retail led her to move to texas from tampa fla where she was president and chief executive of the sweetbay supermarket chain for  years because she believes it is important to experiment with the products she sells in the past year she’s become a “fledgling crafter” inspired by the jewelry her associates and customers make some of which broader says “will rival a boutique” she recently made a pair of turquoise bead and silverwire earrings “i think i got the bug now i have to go buy a bunch of equipment” broader says her children are also becoming crafters recently the family volunteered to create centerpieces for the auction at yearold madison and yearold clay’s school to fit “the louvre” theme they created  eiffel towers each   feet tall and spray painted gold with feathers on top “when the people from the school came to pick them up they asked ‘where did you get these’ as me and my husband were standing there with bandaids on our fingers” broader says “we were like ‘we made them’” it seems broader’s family is not the only one doing crafts together despite the down economy business at michaels is good “there are certain segments of retail that can not only survive but thrive in a downturn economy” broader says she attributes this to the recession encouraging people to return to their roots “people are sort of reconnecting with home right now and simplifying what they’ve done in the past” broader says “so the products we sell and services we provide fit nicely with that” shelley g broader  chicos fas inc  leadership® profile products resources about client support order leadership® profilelast changed  shelley g broader president and 